ðŸŸ¢ Core Java â€“ With Answers
1. Difference between String, StringBuilder, and StringBuffer?
String â†’ Immutable, creates new object if modified.
StringBuilder â†’ Mutable, faster, not thread-safe.
StringBuffer â†’ Mutable, thread-safe (synchronized), slower.
Prefer StringBuilder unless multi-threaded environment.
2. equals() vs == and when to override hashCode()?
== â†’ Compares reference.
equals() â†’ Compares values (if overridden).
Must override hashCode() when overriding equals() to maintain integrity when used inside hash-based collections (like HashMap, HashSet).
3. What is a functional interface?
An interface with only one abstract method. Example:
Copy code
Java
@FunctionalInterface
interface Calculator {
    int add(int a, int b);
}
Can be used with lambda expressions.
4. How does ConcurrentHashMap work?
It divides the map into multiple segments to reduce locking. Prior to Java 8 it used Segment Locking, now it uses CAS (Compare-And-Swap) and locks only affected buckets.
5. What is immutability?
Class whose state cannot change after creation.
Copy code
Java
public final class Employee {
    private final String name;
    public Employee(String name) { this.name = name; }
    public String getName() { return name; }
}
6. Checked vs Unchecked exception?
Checked: Must handle (IOException, SQLException).
Unchecked: Runtime exceptions (NullPointerException, IllegalArgumentException).
7. final, finally, finalize()?
Keyword
Purpose
final
Constant / prevent override
finally
Block that always runs
finalize()
Called before GC (now deprecated)
8. What is ExecutorService?
Manages thread pool â€“ avoids creating separate threads each time.
Copy code
Java
ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(10);
executor.submit(() -> System.out.println("Task"));
executor.shutdown();
9. How does Garbage Collection work?
Automatic memory management using algorithms like mark and sweep. You can trigger hint using System.gc(), but the JVM decides.
10. What is Optional?
Used to avoid NullPointerException.
Copy code
Java
Optional.ofNullable(name).orElse("Default")
ðŸŸ  Spring Boot / Spring Core â€“ With Answers
1. Difference between @Component, @Service, @Repository, @Controller?
Annotation
Usage
@Component
Generic bean
@Service
Business layer
@Repository
DAO layer (adds exception translation)
@Controller
Web layer
2. What is Dependency Injection?
Spring automatically provides required objects instead of the programmer creating them.
3. Bean lifecycle?
Instantiate
Populate properties
@PostConstruct
Use bean
@PreDestroy
Destroy
4. What is @Autowired?
Injects dependencies. Can be done via constructor, setter, or field injection (not recommended).
5. What is inside @SpringBootApplication?
Copy code
Java
@SpringBootConfiguration
@EnableAutoConfiguration
@ComponentScan
6. What is auto-configuration?
Spring Boot inspects the classpath and creates default beans unless overridden.
7. .properties vs .yml?
.yml supports structured data and hierarchies.
.properties is flat.
8. RestTemplate vs WebClient?
Feature
RestTemplate
WebClient
Style
Blocking
Non-blocking
Suitable
Monolith
Microservices
9. How to handle global exception?
Using @ControllerAdvice with @ExceptionHandler.
10. How to create scheduled job?
Copy code
Java
@EnableScheduling
@Scheduled(cron = "0 0/5 * * * ?")
public void job() { ... }
